The transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs) are a group of fatal neurodegenerative diseases which include scrapie in sheep, bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) in cattle and Creutzfeldt to Jacob disease (CJD) in humans. These diseases are thought to be caused by the conversion of a normal cellular glycoprotein (PrPC) into an abnormal disease associated form, PrPSc
